RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRED UP TIGER pressed two wide, vied along with an outer pair of bidders into the far turn, got headed by those foes turning for home, yet fought on through midstretch and forged an advantage in the final sixteenth. LIKEN IT broke outwardly, settled off of the pace in the two path, ranged up outside of the leading trio approaching the far turn, vied four wide around that bend, gained an advantage entering the lane, but drifted out when the rider changed to left handed pressure entering the final sixteenth and was bested by an inner bidder late. FOOLISH STEVE stalked outside of the top pair, bid when an outer rival forced his hand approaching the far turn, vied between horses around that bend, dueled into the final furlong but yielded late. UNCLE BRAD was sent to the fore, dictated terms before vying with a trio of outer bidders into the far turn, but was headed turning for home and gradually gave way. KELLYS THE BOSS lagged well behind the rest and surpassed a tiring rival around the far turn. GOTTAGONOWNOW broke a step slow and steadied when an inner rival cut across her path, advanced to an inside stalking position around the first turn, but chased the leading quartet into the far turn and weakened in the two path around that bend.

DESPEIGHTFUL brushed an outer rival soon after the start before taking contact from that one shortly after, stalked three wide, chased within range along with an outer rival nearing the lane but faded. STORMY COUNTRY DAY broke inwardly and bumped a rival at the start, tracked two wide and between horses into the turn, shifted out turning for home, drifted to the six path in upper stretch and faded.
